The paper discusses the usefulness of PSF in software engineering and reengineering, which falls under the scope of software engineering (cs.SE). PSF is based on ACP, which is a process algebra, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and formal methods (cs.AR). The paper also mentions using PSF at lower abstract levels, which could be related to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and system and control theory (cs.SY).
